### Test Trading APIs - Copy this file and run in VS Code with REST Client extension

### 1. Check if application is running
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health

### 2. Get Available Assets (should return list of tradable assets)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/assets/available

### 3. Check Client Wallet (client 1 should have 10000)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/wallet/1

### 4. Buy Apple Stock (should succeed and create transaction)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/buy?clientId=1&symbol=AAPL&quantity=10&price=175.50

### 5. Check Wallet After Buy (should be 8245.00)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/wallet/1

### 6. Check Asset Holdings (should show AAPL with quantity 10)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/assets/client/1

### 7. Sell Some Apple Stock (should succeed)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/sell?clientId=1&assetId=1&quantity=5&price=180.00

### 8. Check Wallet After Sell (should be 9145.00)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/wallet/1

### 9. Check Final Asset Quantity (should be 5 remaining)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/assets/1

### 10. Test Error - Buy with Insufficient Funds (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/buy?clientId=1&symbol=TSLA&quantity=1000&price=250.00

### 11. Test Error - Invalid Asset Symbol (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/buy?clientId=1&symbol=INVALID&quantity=10&price=100.00

### 12. Test Error - Client Not Found (should fail)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/trading/wallet/999
